e you then.',0,'1','','',0,0),(939,313,'Lance','outlan2000@gmail.com','http://lsdigitaldesign.com','','2009-08-03 11:37:21','2009-08-03 11:37:21','FYI--I\'ve been trying to get some info on BFusion/BFlex to no avail. No one has responded to my submissions to the contact form on the site.\n\nDoes anyone know if this event is actually going to happen this year?',0,'1','','',0,0),(940,314,'Mingo Hagen','email@mingo.nl','http://mingo.nl','','2009-08-04 09:18:00','2009-08-04 09:18:00','while cool, I\'d like to have &lt;cfdocument action=&quot;extracttext&quot;&gt;.',0,'1','','',0,0),(941,314,'Ben Nadel','ben@bennadel.com','http://www.bennadel.com','','2009-08-04 09:19:23','2009-08-04 09:19:23','Awesome! I didn\'t even know ColdFusion could convert word documents into PDFs! Bitchy!',0,'1','','',0,0),(942,314,'John Farrar','johnfarrar@sosensible.com','','','2009-08-04 23:05:57','2009-08-04 23:05:57','Now that has some serious potential. Will have to\nstart dumping and see what pragmatic use this can have! :)',0,'1','','',0,0),(943,314,'Ben Spencer','ben@spencom.com.au','','','2009-08-11 01:57:48','2009-08-11 01:57:48','I havent downloaded CF9 yet, but this example uses .docx as the document format. Can the same be done for the old .doc format which wasn\'t XML based?',0,'1','','',0,0),(944,314,'Terrence Ryan','terry@terrenceryan.com','http://terrenceryan.com','','2009-08-11 16:39:28','2009-08-11 16:39:28','Ben: I haven\'t tested that myself, but I\'m pretty sure we\'ve said it works. ;)',0,'1','','',0,0),(945,314,'Ben Spencer','ben@spencom.com.au','','','2009-08-11 17:27:14','2009-08-11 17:27:14','Thanks Terrence, I read up on it in the end. Yep, it should do .doc quite nicely (with whatever quirks are associated with OpenOffice).\n\nUse #1 for me: Produce thumbnails of word docs for document management application.',0,'1','','',0,0),(946,314,'Juan Escalada','jescalada@portalcreawebs.com','http://www.portalcreawebs.com','','2009-09-22 07:10:17','2009-09-22 07:10:17','Dear Terrence,\n\nA client of mine is asking if a document could be uploaded so that the documents footnotes would be stripped and, together with the associated paragraph, be emailed to different people (As in Footnote 1 and its paragraph goes to Adam for check-up and footnote 2 goes to Joe)...\nI could convince the client to use a PDF if that mad ethings any easier... But Id appreciate your insigt to know wether this would be at all possible...\n\nThanks in advance, Juan Escalada.',0,'1','','',0,0),(947,314,'Don Blaire','cherrywine1000@yahoo.com','','','2010-04-23 19:22:54','2010-04-23 19:22:54','One of our departments downloads a Word doc in which they want to get the content from. This blog was just what I was looking for. Thanks.',0,'1','','',0,0),(948,314,'Tad','tadreeves@gmail.com','http://scientologyparent.wordpress.com/','','2010-05-17 16:02:03','2010-05-17 16:02:03','Terrence - thanks for that.  I\'m trying to use CF9 to pull summary information out of DOCX files.  HWPF doesn\'t do it, wondering if CF9 can do it based on DOCX support.  Do you know the best way of going about such?  Leery to do it by converting to pdf first and then using <CFPDF> to extract, as the summary info (createTime, etc) may have been mangled.',0,'1','','',0,0),(949,314,'Nick','matadorde@yahoo.com','','','2010-08-07 16:49:08','2010-08-07 16:49:08','Just want to confirm that an OpenOffice install on the server is needed to convert word documents to PDFs using coldfusion 9.\n\nPlease correct me if I\'m wrong, but I just ran Terrence\'s code and received a error that an openOffice install was required.',0,'1','','',0,0),(950,314,'Virginia Neal','virginia.neal@courts.wa.gov','http://www.courts.wa.gov','','2010-05-28 19:30:09','2010-05-28 19:30:09','The new extracttext action is nice to have and I am able to use it to simply pull the text of a pdf document.\n\nHowever, I have a real need to keep the general format of the document as well.  This would simply be things line centering, indenting/tabs, line breaks, etc.\n\nI had hoped that using useStructure=\"true\" along with honourspaces=\"true\" would return the basic format of the document, but that does not seem to be the case.\n\nDo you know if it is possible to maintain the basic formatting of a PDF document?\n\nThanks\n\nBTW - the PDF documents that I am working with began as Word and were converted to PDF using your suggested approach (thank you).',0,'1','','',0,0),(951,314,'Cheyenne Throckmorton','cheyenne.throckmorton@gmail.com','http://www.cheyennejack.com','','2010-06-14 16:14:59','2010-06-14 16:14:59','@Virginia\n\nI was running into a similar problem in the last week.  I used an alternative solution that worked in my use case that may or may not help.  I still converted the word documents to pdfs then I used the thumbnail capability to create jpg images at 100% resolution and then displayed those images to the end user which worked well for our use case.\n\nWhile I am looking forward to diving more into the capabilities here and with DDX I think the overall problem we both encountered is that DDX is about the actual content of the pdf devoid of styling, similar to how HTML \"is supposed to be\".  With HTML you add in a CSS file to style, and I believe there is similar type of document that combines with the DDX to create your fully stylized PDF.\n\nThats obviously a lot more work to dig into and I only had the time to do the thumbnail solution for now, but hope that helps.\n\n@Terrence thanks for the blog and great tips that even got me started on solving my use case.',0,'1','','',0,0),(952,314,'Ed','edcheng33@hotmail.com','','','2010-10-18 17:14:07','2010-10-18 17:14:07','Yes you need OpenOffice installed, then add the directory in the admin settings under \'Documents\' section. I tried it w/o the software and it did make a \"pdf\" file but with garbage in it as if you\'re viewing a word doc with textpad.\n\n\"When you use cfdocument to convert a document file, the tag first checks for an OpenOffice installation. When the OpenOffice installation is found, the tag processes the rich text conversion through the OpenOffice libraries.\"\n\nOne odd thing to note is that if the file extension is \'.doc\' it returned garbage (even with openoffice) as the pdf output but with the same file renamed to \".docx\" it worked.',0,'1','','',0,0),(953,314,'vakantiehuis','martijnvanpeper@gmail.com','http://vakantiehuis1.wordpress.com','','2011-02-12 21:31:16','2011-02-12 21:31:16','Leuke site!. Er zijn nog weinig goede sites over dit onderwerp te vinden.\nBen blij met jullie post!\nIk kan helaas geen bookmark aanmaken naar www.terrenceryan.com in Firefox. :( Weten jullie hoe dit komt?\n\nGroetjes Barbara',0,'1','','',0,0),(954,315,'OT','v.rajkumar@gmail.com','','','2009-08-07 07:14:59','2009-08-07 07:14:59','Too bad I cannot access Twitter at work.',0,'1','','',0,0),(955,315,'Charlie Griefer','charlie@griefer.com','http://charlie.griefer.com','','2009-08-07 11:48:33','2009-08-07 11:48:33','Me neither, but I do have my iPhone.  I should get a 30 second grace period on any question I attempt to answer.  Handicap! :)',0,'1','','',0,0),(956,315,'Alirio Boquin','info@alirio.com','http://www.alirio.com/blog','','2009-08-07 12:19:37','2009-08-07 12:19:37','Cool, I try to win, some prize !!!',0,'1','','',0,0),(957,316,'Robert Rawlins','robert.rawlins@thinkbluemedia.co.uk','http://www.thinkbluemedia.co.uk','','2009-08-10 02:58:55','2009-08-10 02:58:55','Yeah this second tour is great news, I missed the SOTR UK for various reasons, I was so glad to see them placing a London date on this second tour, booked my place yesterday, it\'ll be my first CF conference so really looking forward to meeting a few of the \'online\' community face-to-face.\n\nRob',0,'1','','',0,0),(958,318,'Ben Nadel','ben@bennadel.com','http://www.bennadel.com','','2009-08-19 09:14:11','2009-08-19 09:14:11','Nice! I never thought of actually creating a new instance of the CFC. Very cool idea! I always used some hacky approach like dumping out the secret properties of the application scope. Your way is much better!',0,'1','','',0,0),(959,318,'Ben Nadel','ben@bennadel.com','http://www.bennadel.com','','2009-08-19 13:33:58','2009-08-19 13:33:58','Thanks Terry - I was enjoying this post again at lunch :)',0,'1','','',0,0),(960,318,'Ryan Vikander','r.vikander@gmail.com','http://www.twitter.com/rvikander','','2009-08-12 14:35:38','2009-08-12 14:35:38','Maybe I am wrong, but can\'t you just &lt;cfdump var=&quot;#Application#&quot;&gt;?',0,'1','','',0,0),(961,318,'Ryan Vikander','r.vikander@gmail.com','http://www.twitter.com/rvikander','','2009-08-12 14:37:42','2009-08-12 14:37:42','Nevermind, after testing that doesn\'t work.',0,'1','','',0,0),(962,318,'Billy Cravens','bdcravens@gmail.com','http://www.billycravens.com','','2009-08-12 18:34:08','2009-08-12 18:34:08','Since you have to create an object, I\'d think you could\n&lt;cfset test = new Application()&gt;\n&lt;cfdump var=&quot;#test#&quot;&gt;',0,'1','','',0,0),(963,318,'Terrence Ryan','terry@terrenceryan.com','http://terrenceryan.com','','2009-08-19 13:35:43','2009-08-19 13:35:43','Thanks, Ben. I\'m glad you liked it.  It was one of those &quot;It\'s so simple it can\'t work&quot; moments.',0,'1','','',0,0),(964,318,'joe banken','jbanken@gmail.com','http://jbanken.blogspot.com/','','2009-09-19 11:07:55','2009-09-19 11:07:55','Thats pretty cool man, I also did not know you could  do new Application(). Nice find.',0,'1','','',0,0),(965,319,'Marcos Placona','marcos.placona@gmail.com','http://www.placona.co.uk/blog','','2009-08-18 04:10:28','2009-08-18 04:10:28','Very well done Terry. I\'ll make sure to spread it to the world! Thanks again!',0,'1','','',0,0),(966,319,'Mike Henke','henke.mike@gmail.com','http://www.henke.ws','','2009-08-18 07:30:08','2009-08-18 07:30:08','This is a great announcement.',0,'1','','',0,0),(967,319,'Mark Phillips','mark@vertabase.com','http://www.vertabase.com','','2009-08-20 11:20:19','2009-08-2