ce later. ','Migrated to Google App Engine','I just upgraded to Google App Engine, and I liked it. ','inherit','open','open','','696-revision-v1','','','2014-08-27 14:26:15','2014-08-27 14:26:15','',696,'https://digital-axon-666.appspot.com/blog/index.php/696-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(705,1,'2014-10-14 16:08:31','2014-10-14 16:08:31','After <a href=\"http://terrenceryan.com/blog/index.php/hello-adobe/\">5 years</a>, Wednesday October 15th is my last day with Adobe. Its fitting that my last duty for Adobe is a round of sessions at Max 2014. For me Max is the pinnacle of outreach at Adobe.  As an audience member you get access to engineers, product mangers, and other experts from the community. My first had a profound impact on me. The very first entry on my blog is about <a href=\"http://terrenceryan.com/blog/index.php/back_from_maxx/\">Max 2004</a> - 10 years ago. The industry and what the event was all about was very different - back then, I was in the audience learning about ColdFusion, Flex and Flashpaper from Macromedia.  This year I was  on stage speaking about designer workflows using hosted cloud services for Adobe.  Its a very different world.\r\n\r\nFive years after my first Max I got my dream job and joined Adobe. In the past 5 years, Ive traveled over 560,000 miles to 119 or so cities. Ive made friends all over the globe. And Ive had a front view seats to some of the craziest technology fights weve ever seen. Ive represented multiple technologies: ColdFusion, Flex, Flash, HTML5 and Creative Cloud.  Ive played with great toys. Ive met most of my technical heroes along the way. Its been a fun ride. \r\n\r\nAnd now Im leaving. \r\n\r\nTo all my friends Ive met along the way, it was fantastic to have the privilege of talking technology with you all, and I hope to see you in the future. Keep in touch.   \r\n\r\nTo my co-workers, its been a pleasure working with you. \r\n\r\nTo Adobe itself, youve been a great place to work, learn, and grow. So long and thanks for all the fish.    \r\n\r\nI have a next step planned. But in keeping with <a href=\"http://terrenceryan.com/blog/index.php/goodbye-wharton/\">my traditions</a>, I wanted to keep this a maudlin post about whats behind me, rather than talk about whats next. Ill be blogging about that soon enough. \r\n','Goodbye Adobe...','I\'m leaving Adobe. ','publish','open','open','','goodbye-adobe','','','2014-10-22 02:39:11','2014-10-22 02:39:11','',0,'https://digital-axon-666.appspot.com/blog/?p=705',0,'post','',0),(706,1,'2014-10-14 15:45:06','2014-10-14 15:45:06','After <a href=\"http://terrenceryan.com/blog/index.php/hello-adobe/\">5 years</a>, Wednesday October 15th is my last day with Adobe. Its fitting that my last duty for Adobe is a round of sessions at Max 2014. For me Max is the pinnacle of outreach at Adobe.  As an audience member you get access to engineers, product mangers, and other experts from the community. My first had a profound impact on me. The very first entry on my blog is about <a href=\"http://terrenceryan.com/blog/index.php/back_from_maxx/\">Max 2004</a> - 10 years ago. The industry and what the event was all about was very different - back then, I was in the audience learning about ColdFusion, Flex and Flashpaper from Macromedia.  This year I was  on stage speaking about designer workflows using hosted cloud services for Adobe.  Its a very different world.\r\n\r\nFive years after my first Max I got my dream job and joined Adobe. In the past 5 years, Ive traveled over 560,000 miles to 119 or so cities. Ive made friends all over the globe. And Ive had a front view seats to some of the craziest technology fights weve ever seen. Ive represented multiple technologies: ColdFusion, Flex, Flash, HTML5 and Creative Cloud.  Ive played with great toys. Ive met most of my technical heroes along the way. Its been a fun ride. \r\n\r\nAnd now Im leaving. \r\n\r\nTo all my friends Ive met along the way, it was fantastic to have the privilege of talking technology with you all, and I hope to see you in the future. Keep in touch.   \r\n\r\nTo my co-workers, its been a pleasure working with you. \r\n\r\nTo Adobe itself, youve been a great place to work, learn, and grow. So long and thanks for all the fish.    \r\n\r\nI have a next step planned. But in keeping with <a href=\"http://terrenceryan.com/blog/index.php/goodbye-wharton/\">my traditions</a>, I wanted to keep this a maudlin post about whats behind me, rather than talk about whats next. Ill be blogging about that soon enough. \r\n','Goodbye Adobe...','I\'m leaving Adobe. ','inherit','open','open','','705-revision-v1','','','2014-10-14 15:45:06','2014-10-14 15:45:06','',705,'https://digital-axon-666.appspot.com/blog/index.php/705-revision-v1/',0,'revision','',0),(707,1,'2014-10-14 16:04:24','2014-10-14 16:04:24','<a href=\"https://00e9e64bacda24f4bf29512bd999b3589ceb1d49cbdd16bdb6-apidata.googleusercontent.com/download/storage/v1_internal/b/digital-axon-666.appspot.com/o/L2FwcGhvc3RpbmdfcHJvZC9ibG9icy9BRW5CMlVwZ1lfYmZCaGlKVUVna2pJUEVjVDc1TWVrN09kNktQeHFOTGtUcGtMRWxma2xEcFM3ZG9GeURWMXF3WEs1WnRuc09DeW0zbXRaaVl2UGZXa1pKeE9UZ0RpM0ZjUS5VeG5pQVZzSHFhZ2Zwa0J2?qk=AD5uMEvfj4YIkV9pokZSj3ml73OFgruyVOX2tv41F5Bn8ReSI3QXwMsnyhYpmOhGyQGxRbRo4LLHc1a5M9hVwiupkrQ797m1YgP1liS6PsRy5wS08T01w8Wy80AQ-MzJWmzJsZ0qgKg86cxVClXfIOtQWnq8k_0UzVPZ32yfRSwMrxGc22aMiMR-l4-h6xInlorNKgkY4vPeQ5gje54NJ_-iqNOudrAH8UMtjY2mnfpMCOzCam2UYerI3Ms6cat50EgUeH12c0T3UqNDkFL2Ou5ArVZWeHX7ot4XcylAFHTPsIUDrbo3zKpu6xqQ9ddmajrA19FWoPBNphGgXfb7U4QvPmdrlRFHoj4l9YhpnIjLznL1mXbJl-Yra6uxM4UP2xuBUKU_abzPrSfFd3w3bT-4-HK-KmBG27nOaGdYaudYkr4WI3cYkLoE1b60zWZD-Cy8y8lON55wfN0l2Q9_rYBvbZXKVeDViXexfJTpZx16ZUzhsLjpR7u7dE0EMbS6ybFma6LYK64A4g05Uva4fgrDROuP7H84thKxA_24zhjK3mIY5_f7LP32KiVqm9Zpw0JjaOKY93VOweiBEpmtMdRml9gnPJjYi7J6gylebVPNIWHBdlGMZx0J0l7fhoRLvuVYnNS4i6NrW7htsnjF3cwNIDES_dBZONRH63ftpRO_s8BHjAG1iiB9gLLLfsfjtjMuBiwg9HgicMdgqC1hZjkAlSX3RdiXBmocjaKrtPRv8t9prkOEVM4Q5AxdNdQWqBZe910jsJtdAGvQpVwmP1rp7_qGCIjuDl03ndq6-JCIvE1t-PVBIVzBqA